# Environment Variables Template

## AWS Credentials (local development)
```bash
# Set in ~/.aws/credentials or via 'aws configure'
[default]
aws_access_key_id = YOUR_ACCESS_KEY_ID
aws_secret_access_key = YOUR_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
```

## Amplify Backend Environment Variables

### uploadHandler Lambda
```
STORAGE_PLANTDISEASESTORAGE_BUCKET=plantdisease-storage-prod-xxxxx
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
```

### validateImageHandler Lambda
```
STORAGE_PLANTDISEASESTORAGE_BUCKET=plantdisease-storage-prod-xxxxx
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
```

### predictHandler Lambda
```
STORAGE_PLANTDISEASESTORAGE_BUCKET=plantdisease-storage-prod-xxxxx
SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME=plant-disease-endpoint
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
```

### saveAnnotationHandler Lambda
```
STORAGE_PLANTDISEASESTORAGE_BUCKET=plantdisease-storage-prod-xxxxx
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
```

## React Frontend (.env.local - optional for local dev)
```
REACT_APP_API_ENDPOINT=https://your-api-id.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod
REACT_APP_S3_BUCKET=plantdisease-storage-prod-xxxxx
```

## SageMaker Endpoint Configuration
Set after deploying your SageMaker endpoint:
```bash
amplify update function
# Select: predictHandler
# Add SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT_NAME and redeploy with: amplify push
```

## AWS Region
Default: `us-east-1` (can be changed during `amplify init`)

## Notes
- Never commit credentials to Git
- Use AWS IAM roles for production
- Rotate credentials quarterly
- Use separate AWS accounts for dev/prod
